# PERPETUAL SOFTWARE LICENSE ACQUISITION AGREEMENT

## 1. DEFINITIONS

**"Licensor"** refers to the owner and developer of the Software.

**"Licensee"** refers to the natural person or legal entity that has legitimately acquired the Software.

**"Software"** refers to the computer program/application identified as camu - generic site adaptable to the client, all versions, including all related documentation.

**"Use"** refers to the installation, access, execution, storage, or viewing of the Software.

## 2. LICENSE GRANT

Upon full payment of the license fee, the Licensor grants the Licensee a perpetual, non-exclusive, and non-transferable license to use the Software, according to the terms and conditions established in this document.

Only those who have legitimately acquired this license may use this Software.

## 3. RIGHTS GRANTED TO THE LICENSEE

The Licensee who has legitimately acquired the Software has the right to:

3.1. Use the Software on any compatible device owned or controlled by the Licensee.

3.2. Study the functioning of the Software, including adaptation for their specific needs.

3.3. Modify the Software for personal use, including without having to pay additional fees for any modifications if these are made with the licensee's resources.

3.4. Make backup copies of the Software.

3.5. Receive not only the compiled Software itself, but also its source code for use in future modifications or adaptations with the aim of supplying and serving only their own needs or those of their direct clients.

3.6. Host the Software on their own servers or on cloud hosting services for public use, provided that the purpose is to make the Software available for the use of the Licensee or their direct clients, and not for redistribution of the Software itself.

## 4. RESTRICTIONS

4.1. The Licensee MAY NOT redistribute, sell, rent, lend, or transfer the Software or its source code to any person who has not legitimately acquired the Software. For the avoidance of doubt, the Licensee may host the Software on local or cloud servers to make it available as a website.

4.2. The Licensee may not remove or alter any copyright notices, trademarks, or other proprietary notices from the Software.

4.3. The Licensee may not use the Software to develop competing products or services.

## 5. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY

5.1. The Software, including source code, structure, organization, user interface, documentation, and design, is the exclusive property of the Licensor and is protected by copyright laws and other intellectual property laws.

5.2. This license does not transfer to the Licensee any title or ownership of the Software, only the right of use as specified in this document.

5.3. Any modifications, adaptations, or derivative works of the Software made by the Licensee remain the intellectual property of the Licensor.

## 6. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY

UNDER NO CIRCUMSTANCES WILL THE LICENSOR BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT DAMAGES, INCLUDING LOSS OF PROFITS, LOSS OF DATA, BUSINESS INTERRUPTION, OR OTHER COMMERCIAL LOSSES.

## 7. TERMINATION OF LICENSE

7.1. This license will remain in effect until terminated by the Licensee or the Licensor.

7.2. The Licensor may terminate this license if the Licensee violates any of the terms and conditions. In case of termination, the Licensee must destroy all copies of the Software in their possession.

7.3. The Licensee may terminate this license if the Licensor violates any of the terms and conditions. In case of termination, the Licensee must destroy all copies of the Software in their possession, and the Licensor must refund the amount paid for the license to the Licensee.

